
Used by the Freedom Toaster project, the term "toaster" refers to a self-contained software package (or "appliance") that is easily distributable by electronic means.Freedom Toaster website This use generally connotes free software and is a term occasionally used in the open source software community."Toaster Full for qmail websiteOpen Video Toaster website
A toaster appliance is often made up of software components that were not originally packaged together. The new toaster package provides a co-ordinated packaging framework in which all the components can function together as a self-contained unit.

